<definition>
    <statement>
        <p>Two vectors <m>\vec u</m> and <m>\vec v</m> in <m>\IR^n</m> are <term>orthogonal</term><idx>orthogonal</idx> provided <m>\vec u \cdot \vec v = 0</m>.
        </p></statement></definition>

<p>A bunch of stuff goes here. So it turns out you can find the angle between vectors using the Law of Cosines as a starting place.</p>   

    
    

